# Timeline Recalculation Model

This experiment simulates a simple universe evolving over time.  
The evolution rule depends on an external quantum-like parameter E.

Two timelines are generated:

1. Timeline A: using E = E0
2. Timeline B: using E = E1 (external condition changed)

The goal is to observe how sensitive the internal history is to external conditions,  
and whether the "past" of the system can be reshaped when the external layer changes.

This models the idea of a simulated universe where the internal timeline is not fixed,  
but depends on higher-level constraints.
